Package energy.usef.core.data.xml.bean.message

Message class interfaces.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Message
    Interface which needs to be implemented for all Messages.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Adapter1  
    Adapter2  
    Adapter3  
    Adapter4  
    Aggregator
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    CommonReferenceQuery
    CommonReferenceQuery is used by DSOs to discover which Aggregators represent which number of Connections on its registered Congestion Point(s).
    CommonReferenceQueryResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a CommonReferenceQuery message, the receiving implementation must reply with a CommonReferenceQueryResponse, indicating whether the query executed successfully, and if it did, including the query results.
    CommonReferenceUpdate
    CommonReferenceUpdate is used by the DSO to declare a Congestion Point and registering the Connection(s) associated with it (or, if the Connection count is 0, to delete the Congestion Point).
    CommonReferenceUpdateResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a CommonReferenceUpdate message, the receiving implementation must reply with a CommonReferenceUpdateResponse, indicating whether the update was handled successfully.
    CongestionPoint
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Connection
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    ConnectionMeterData
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    ConnectionMeterEvent
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Connections
    This element is used in meter data queries to represent a group of connections, linked to a parent (Congestion Point or BRP).
    FlexBase
    FlexBase elements are the basis for the various Flex* messages, such as FlexRequest, FlexOffer and FlexOrder, and contain all attributes common to those messages.
    FlexOffer
    FlexOffer messages are used by Aggregators to make DSOs and BRPs an offer for providing flexibility.
    FlexOfferResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a FlexOffer message, the receiving implementation must reply with a FlexOfferResponse, indicating whether the flex offer was processed successfully.
    FlexOfferRevocation
    The FlexOfferRevocation message is used by the Aggegator to revoke a FlexOffer previously sent to a DSO or BRP.
    FlexOfferRevocationResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a FlexOfferRevocation message, the receiving implementation must reply with a FlexOfferRevocationResponse, indicating whether the revocation was handled successfully.
    FlexOrder
    FlexOrder messages are used by DSOs and BRPs to purchase flexibility from an Aggregator based on a previous FlexOffer.
    FlexOrderResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a FlexOrder message, the receiving implementation must reply with a FlexOrderResponse, indicating whether the update was handled successfully.
    FlexOrderSettlement
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    FlexOrderSettlementStatus
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    FlexOrderStatus
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    FlexRequest
    FlexRequest messages are used by BRPs and DSOs to request flexibility from Aggregators.
    FlexRequestResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a FlexRequest message, the receiving implementation must reply with a FlexRequestResponse, indicating whether the flex request was processed successfully.
    MessageMetadata
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MeterData
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MeterDataQuery
    MeterDataQuery is used by customers of a Meter Data Company to query per-Connection, per-PTU power consumption/production values for a specified period.
    MeterDataQueryResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a MeterDataQuery message, the receiving implementation must reply with a MeterDataQueryResponse, indicating whether the query executed successfully, and if it did, including the query results.
    MeterDataSet
    This element is used in meter data responses to represent a group of meter data entries, linked to a parent (Congestion Point or BRP).
    ObjectFactory
    This object contains factory methods for each Java content interface and Java element interface generated in the energy.usef.core.data.xml.bean.message package.
    Prognosis
    Prognosis messages are used to communicate A-plans and D-prognoses between USEF participants.
    PrognosisResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a Prognosis message, the receiving implementation must reply with a PrognosisResponse, indicating whether the prognosis was syntactically and semantically valid, and, in case any FlexOrder messages have previously been sent for any PTU in the Period the Prognosis applies to, a FlexOrderStatus indication for each of those orders.
    PTU
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    PTUMeterData
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    PTUSettlement
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    SettlementMessage
    The SettlementMessage is sent by DSOs and BRPs on a regular basis (typically monthly) to AGRs in order to initiate settlement.
    SettlementMessageResponse
    Upon receiving and processing a SettlementMessage, the receiving implementation must reply with a SettlementMessageResponse, indicating whether the initial message was handled successfully.
    SignedMessage
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    SignedMessageReply
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    TestMessage
    TestMessage does not have any content (other than the mandatory message metadata) and may be used by implementations for (connectivity) testing purposes.
    TestMessageResponse
    Upon receiving a TestMessage, the receiving implementation must reply with a TestMessageResponse.
